project.name: Lich.sc
project.description: SuperCollider bindings for the Lich live coding language.

dc.name: dc
example:
let test value => dc value >> out 0
let t = test 1
stop t

sin.name: sin
example:
let test f => sin f >> out 0
let t = test 440
stop t

saw.name: saw
example:
let test f => saw f >> out 0
let t = test 440
stop t

tri.name: tri
example:
let test f => tri f >> out 0
let t = test 440
stop t

square.name: square
example:
let test f => square f >> out 0
let t = test 440
stop t

pulse.name: pulse
pulse.description: A pulse wave oscillator with variable duty cycle.
example:
let test f w => pulse f w >> out 0
let t = test 440 0.2
stop t

blip.name: blip
blip.description: An oscillator with a variable number of harmonics of equal amplitude.
example:
let test f n => blip f n >> out 0
let t = test 440 5
stop t

formant.name: formant
formant.description: Generates a set of harmonics around a formant frequency at a given fundamental frequency.

params.name: bwf
params.description: Pulse width frequency. Must be >= fundf.

example:
let test fund form bwf => blip fund form bwf >> out 0
let t = test 440 1760 880
stop t

impulse.name: impulse
impulse.description: Generates single sample impulses at a frequency.
example:
let test f => impulse f >> out 0
let t = test 5
stop t

white.name: white
example:
let test a => white a >> out 0
let t = test 1
stop t

pink.name: pink
example:
let test a => pink a >> out 0
let t = test 1
stop t

brown.name: brown
example:
let test a => brown a >> out 0
let t = test 1
stop t

gray.name: gray
example:
let test a => gray a >> out 0
let t = test 1
stop t

clipNoise.name: clipNoise
clipNoise.description: Generates noise whose values are either -1 or 1.
example:
let test a => clipNoise a >> out 0
let t = test 1
stop t

crackle.name: crackle
crackle.description: A noise generator based on a chaotic function.

params.name: chaos
params.description: A parameter of the chaotic function with useful values from just below 1.0 to just above 2.0. Towards 2.0 the sound crackles.

example:
let test c => crackle c >> out 0
let t = test 1.5
stop t

dust.name: dust

params.name: density
params.description: Average number of impulses per second.

example:
let test d => dust d >> out 0
let t = test 1.5
stop t

noiseN.name: noiseN
example:
let test f => noiseN f >> out 0
let t = test 440
stop t

noiseL.name: noiseL
noiseL.description: A linearly interpolated random number generator
example:
let test f => noiseL f >> out 0
let t = test 440
stop t

noiseX.name: noiseX
noiseX.description: A cubic interpolated random number generator
example:
let test f => noiseX f >> out 0
let t = test 440
stop t

cuspN.name: cuspN
cuspN.description: A non-interpolating sound generator based on the difference equation: x[n+1] = a - b * sqrt(abs(x[n]))
example:
let test f a b xi => cuspN f a b xi >> out 0
let t = test 22050 1 1.9 0
stop t

cuspL.name: cuspL
cuspL.description: A linearly interpolating sound generator based on the difference equation: x[n+1] = a - b * sqrt(abs(x[n]))
example:
let test f a b xi => cuspL f a b xi >> out 0
let t = test 22050 1 1.9 0
stop t

gbmanN.name: gbmanN
gbmanN.description: A non-interpolating sound generator based on the difference equation: x[n+1] = 1 - y[n] + abs(x[n]); y[n+1] = x[n];
example:
let test f xi yi => gbmanN f xi yi >> out 0
let t = test 22050 1.2 2.1
stop t

gbmanL.name: gbmanL
gbmanL.description: A linearly interpolating sound generator based on the difference equation: x[n+1] = 1 - y[n] + abs(x[n]); y[n+1] = x[n];
example:
let test f xi yi => gbmanL f xi yi >> out 0
let t = test 22050 1.2 2.1
stop t

lowpass.name: lowpass
example:
let test f q => white 1 >> lowpass f q >> out 0
let t = test 440 10
stop t

highpass.name: highpass
example:
let test f q => white 1 >> highpass f q >> out 0
let t = test 440 10
stop t

bandpass.name: bandpass
example:
let test f q => white 1 >> bandpass f q >> out 0
let t = test 440 10
stop t

lag.name: lag
lag.description: Ramp a signal between two values over time.
example:
let test lagtime => noiseN 100 >> lag lagtime >> out 0
let t = test 0.001
stop t

crush.name: crush
example:
let test b => sin 440 >> crush b >> out 0
let t = test 4
stop t

decimate.name: decimate
decimate.description: Sample rate reduction on a signal.
example:
let test r => sin 440 >> decimate r >> out 0
let t = test 11000
stop t

allpassN.name: allpassN
allpassN.description: An allpass delay line with no interpolation.

params.name: decay
params.description: Time for the echoes to decay by 60 decibels.

example:
let test del => impulse 1 >> allpassN del del 1 >> out 0
let t = test 0.1
stop t

allpassL.name: allpassL
allpassL.description: An allpass delay line with linear interpolation.

params.name: decay
params.description: Time for the echoes to decay by 60 decibels.

example:
let test del => impulse 1 >> allpassL del del 1 >> out 0
let t = test 0.1
stop t

allpassC.name: allpassC
allpassC.description: An allpass delay line with cubic interpolation.

params.name: decay
params.description: Time for the echoes to decay by 60 decibels.

example:
let test del => impulse 1 >> allpassC del del 1 >> out 0
let t = test 0.1
stop t

combN.name: combN
combN.description: A comb delay line with no interpolation.

params.name: decay
params.description: Time for the echoes to decay by 60 decibels.

example:
let test del => impulse 1 >> combN del del 1 >> out 0
let t = test 0.1
stop t

combL.name: combL
combL.description: A comb delay line with linear interpolation.

params.name: decay
params.description: Time for the echoes to decay by 60 decibels.

example:
let test del => impulse 1 >> combL del del 1 >> out 0
let t = test 0.1
stop t

combC.name: combC
combC.description: A comb delay line with cubic interpolation.

params.name: decay
params.description: Time in seconds for the echoes to decay by 60 decibels.

example:
let test del => impulse 1 >> combC del del 1 >> out 0
let t = test 0.1
stop t

delayN.name: delayN
delayN.description: A simple delay with no interpolation.
example:
let test del => impulse 1 >> delayN del del >> out 0
let t = test 0.1
stop t

delayL.name: delayL
delayL.description: A simple delay with linear interpolation.
example:
let test del => impulse 1 >> delayL del del >> out 0
let t = test 0.1
stop t

delayC.name: delayC
delayC.description: A simple delay with cubic interpolation.
example:
let test del => impulse 1 >> delayC del del >> out 0
let t = test 0.1
stop t

env.name: env
env.description: Envelope generator. Used for amplitude envelopes, will automatically free the synth when finished.

params.name: levels
params.description: The levels that the envelope will move through

params.name: times
params.description: The times it takes for the env to move between levels. Should be 1 item less than levels

params.name: shape
params.description: Either a shape number or string. Some examples: -4, 0, 1, "linear", "squared"

example:
let test amp => white amp >> env [0,1,0] [1,1] "linear" >> out 0
test $ random 0.1 1.0

env2.name: env2
env2.description: Envelope generator. Used for amplitude envelopes, will NOT automatically free the synth when finished.

params.name: levels
params.description: The levels that the envelope will move through

params.name: times
params.description: The times it takes for the env to move between levels. Should be 1 item less than levels

params.name: shape
params.description: Either a shape number or string. Some examples: -4, 0, 1, "linear", "squared"

example:
let test f => sin (env2[f,f*2,f] [1,1] "linear" 1) >> env [0,0.3,0] [2,2] "linear" >> out 0
test $ random 440 880

perc.name: perc
perc.description: Envelope generator. Used for amplitude envelopes, will automatically free the synth when finished.

params.name: attackTime
params.description: Time for the envelope to go from 0 to the peak

params.name: peak
params.description: The highest level the envelope with reach

params.name: decayTime
params.description: Time for the envelope to go from the peak to 0

example:
let test amp => white amp >> perc 0 1 1 >> out 0
test $ random 0.1 1.0

perc2.name: perc2
perc2.description: Envelope generator. Used for amplitude envelopes, will NOT automatically free the synth when finished.

params.name: attackTime
params.description: Time for the envelope to go from 0 to the peak

params.name: peak
params.description: The highest level the envelope with reach

params.name: decayTime
params.description: Time for the envelope to go from the peak to 0

out.name: out
out.description: Send a signal to an output bus.

params.name: busNum
params.description: The bus index to send to

example:
let test bus => white 1 >> out bus
let t = test 0
stop t
